At 08:51 PM 8/21/2008, Jamie wrote...
>what I have done for my radio circuit is use the ground in the key 
>circuit
>that the key buzzer uses to complete the circuit for another relay.

That's a good solution, but the relay should be unnecessary. Every head 
unit I've ever run into draws it's power from the constant +12V lead, 
and the switched lead only serves as a low current signal to turn on. 
You can tell by the fuse sizes because the constant lead will have a 
bigger fuse. 
